definition: not to have access/beyond one's authority or capability/sth one has no way of doing

from/through/via/to follow/to obey/to engage in (an activity)/never (in negative sentence)/(Taiwan pr. [zong4]) retainer/assistant/auxiliary/subordinate/related by common paternal grandfather or earlier ancestor
like mice trying to pull a turtle, nowhere to get a hand grip (idiom)/no clue where to start
pinyin: lao3 shu3 la1 gui1 , wu2 cong2 xia4 shou3

sentences.english: But beyond that his imagination could not travel.
sentences.chinese: 除此之外，他的想像力就无从驰骋了。

sentences.english: Big problem or does not know how to start, or solution is not complete.
sentences.chinese: 大题要么无从下手，要么解不全。

sentences.english: We had to push the car home as it broke down half way and we couldst know how to repair it.
sentences.chinese: 半路上车抛锚了，我们又无从修理，只得将其推回。

sentences.english: The Libyan air campaign could not have been fought without American help.
sentences.chinese: 离开美国的帮助，利比亚空战也无从展开。

sentences.english: Without a peaceful and stable environment, there is no development to speak of.
sentences.chinese: 没有和平稳定的环境，发展无从谈起。

sentences.english: Love, in all its endlessness , unboundedness and failed definitions is this experience.
sentences.chinese: 这是一次无边无境，无从定义的爱之旅。

sentences.english: So many things happened without any choice;
sentences.chinese: 许多事情，无从选择地发生。

sentences.english: The past cannot be changed. The future is yet in your power.
sentences.chinese: 过往已无从改变，但未来仍握于你手。

sentences.english: The question is whether he is alive or dead. There is no trace of him.
sentences.chinese: 问题是是他是生还是死我们无从得知他的行踪。

sentences.english: “We never know what the answer will be,” says Mr Smith.
sentences.chinese: “我们无从猜测答案会是什么，”史密斯先生说。

sentences.english: Without this point, no discussion can be started.
sentences.chinese: 没有这一点，所有的讨论都无从谈起。

sentences.english: Because rock keeps silence which makes instigator don't know what to do with it.
sentences.chinese: 因为石头的静默令挑衅生事者无从入手。

sentences.english: The long-term effects of inhaling contaminated air is unknown.
sentences.chinese: 长期吸入被污染空气的影响还无从知晓。

sentences.english: As you look around your room or entire house for that matter it seems impossible.
sentences.chinese: 你四下打量你的房间或是整个屋子，看来无从下手。

sentences.english: It's unknown how profitable Harbin Pharmaceutical Group Sixth Pharm Plant is.
sentences.chinese: 哈药六厂的盈利状况我们无从得知。

sentences.english: Do you ever feel overwhelmed or have too much to do?
sentences.chinese: 你是否感到不知所措或是工作太多无从下手？

definition: at a loss/unable to do anything about it/to have no choice
not knowing anything at all (idiom); completely ignorant/without an inkling
just a word or two (idiom); a few isolated phrases
to mention sth without elaborating (idiom); not giving details
see 謎兒|谜儿[mei4 r5], riddle
unable to reach a decision (idiom); cannot agree on the right choice/no unanimous decision/still a matter of discussion
what is true and what is fake
